criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age between 18 and 70 years old;

          -  ability to sign the informed consent form;

          -  ability to understand the instructions and to complete the motor task;

          -  voluntary knee flexion-extension range of at least 70°;

          -  maximal extension of angle < 30° (0°=full extension, 180° sagittal tibio-femural
             angle).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  pregnancy;

          -  a history of epilepsy (to avoid the risk for seizures triggered by the stimuli);

          -  Mini Mental State Examination ≤27/30;

          -  implanted electro-sensitive devices;

          -  any orthopedic condition limiting the articular mobility or muscular strength of the
             lower limbs;

          -  current treatment with oral anticoagulant therapy (to avoid the risk for muscle
             hemorrhage);

          -  medium/serius osteoporosis (femoral Bone Mineral Density on the affected side, t-score
             < (-3.5));

          -  familiarity with the testing method.
